ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I recommend this course to fellow students.
If the student is really keen on the subject.

I would recommend it. This is a topic all computer scientists must know because it pops up everywhere. Moreover the concepts are both deep and very elegant. Being in love with clever mathematics I can only recommend it.
Can achieve lots of knowledges related to computational complexity. The workload is not light, but challenging. I think the class is a good opportunity to learn computational complexity.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course helped with my breadth requirements, but not with my research.
I did not know anything about this field, it gave me an enjoyable overview of the field with some dives into quite precise topics like randomized complexity.
